item.description:
Did you know that the largest living organism in the world is not a whale, elephant, or even a dinosaur , but a fugus?The Armillaria ostoyae,also known as the honey mushrom, covers an area of over 2,200 acres(8,9 square kilometers) i Oregon's Blue Mountains. This massive organism is estimated to be around 2,400 years old and is still growing to this day. While it may not be the most glamorous or well-known organism, the honey mushroom is a estament to the incredible diversity and complexity of life on our planet.
